<p>Now when we go back and refresh, no problems. The <code>genus_scientist</code> table now holds
the original entry we created and this <em>one</em> new entry: no duplicates for us.</p>
<p>Next mission: if I have a <code>Genus</code>, how can I get and print of all of its related
Users? AND, what if I have a <code>User</code>, how can I get its related Genuses? This will
take us down the magical - but dangerous - road of <em>inverse</em> relationships.</p>

    
